chemistry to amino acid synthesis. Used in Michael addition, Strecker synthesis, cyanosulfidic pathway, and glycine synthesis.", "incoming_reactions": [], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_012", "rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_017"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_009", "description": "Formaldehyde: C1 building block hub bridging hydrothermal and surface environments. Produced by Fischer-Tropsch-type reduction of formate on magnetite; feeds into both acrolein synthesis and glycine Strecker synthesis.", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_010"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_011", "rxn_017"]}]}, "reasoning": "", "duration_ms": 556116.7166233063, "success": true, "error_message": null}
