nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Glutamate\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network models the prebiotic synthesis of glutamate through two major convergence paradigms: (1) the iron-sulfur world / reverse TCA cycle analog producing \u03b1-ketoglutarate, which is then aminated via three distinct mechanisms (mineral-catalyzed transamination, NADH-mediated reductive amination, and direct hydrothermal reductive amination), and (2) the cyanosulfidic / Strecker paradigm producing 2-aminopentanedinitrile, which is hydrolyzed to glutamate via two distinct routes (direct hydrolysis and cyanamide-assisted hydrolysis). The rTCA pathway is expanded stepwise through C2\u2192C3\u2192C4\u2192C5 intermediates on specific mineral surfaces (greigite, magnetite, pyrite, pyrrhotite) following W\u00e4chtersh\u00e4user's iron-sulfur world and Menor-Salv\u00e1n et al. (2013). The Strecker/cyanosulfidic pathways follow Sutherland (2016) and the Miller-Urey reanalyses of Johnson et al. (2008) and Parker et al. (2014). A pyroglutamate stabilization cycle captures the thermal cycling behavior documented in hydrothermal stability studies. Environmental flow runs from Hydrothermal (CO2 fixation, mineral catalysis) through Surface (Strecker, cyanosulfidic, UV photochemistry) to Biochemical (NADH reductive amination, final assembly).\n\nMOLECULES (24 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen gas) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_005: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_007: CO (carbon monoxide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: CHO2- (formate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: CH2O (formaldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O (acrolein) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H5NO (3-cyanopropanal) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: